title: Virgin Galactic sets late June date for first commercial SpaceShipTwo flight
summary: Virgin Galactic announced June 15 that it plans to conduct the first commercial flight of its SpaceShipTwo suborbital vehicle in late June on a mission for the Italian Air Force.

title: Virgin Galactic sets first commercial space tourism flight for this month; shares spike more than 40%
summary: Virgin Galactic aims to launch its commercial space tourism service in late June.

title: Virgin Galactic To Begin Commercial Operations This Month
summary: Virgin Galactic has announced their are preparing for the first commercial flight of the SpaceShipTwo suborbital vehicle in later this month.

title: Virgin Galactic sets date and announces crew for first commercial SpaceShipTwo flight
summary: Virgin Galactic plans to conduct its first fully commercial flight of its SpaceShipTwo suborbital spaceplane on June 29, carrying three Italians who will conduct more than a dozen experiments.

title: Launch Roundup: SpaceX to launch Euclid; Virgin Galactic to fly crewed suborbital mission
summary: Four launches are planned for the week of June 24 to July 1. The Russians are planning to launch a Meteor weather satellite aboard a Soyuz rocket on Tuesday, June 27, and Virgin Galactic plans to fly its Galactic 01 crewed suborbital mission no earlier than Thursday, June 29. Firefly’s Alpha rocket is thought to be making its first operational flight with the DARPA Victus Nox mission no earlier than the last week of June, and SpaceX plans to end the week with the launch of the European Space Agency’s (ESA) Euclid telescope for on Saturday, July 1.
